LOCUS       HDM_N2_genscript        5972 bp DNA     circular SYN 09-NOV-2023
DEFINITION  synthetic circular DNA.
ACCESSION   .
VERSION     .
KEYWORDS    .
SOURCE      synthetic DNA construct
  ORGANISM  synthetic DNA construct
REFERENCE   1  (bases 1 to 5972)
  AUTHORS   .
  TITLE     Direct Submission
  JOURNAL   Exported Nov 9, 2023 from SnapGene 7.0.3
            https://www.snapgene.com
COMMENT     I (Jesse Bloom) created this plasmid.  It is an HDM plasmid where 
            inserts can be cloned into a 5' NotI site and a 3' BamHI site.  I 
            created this plasmid by cutting the VSVG out of  HDM-VSVG with 
            EcoRI.   CHARACTERIZATION: * Confirmed by sequencing region from nt 
            1234 - 2068 (1-22-08) Kate cloned IDT codon optimized SARS-CoV-2 
            Spike into plasmid 44 after digesting with EcoRI and HindIII. Kate 
            inserted a 'cgccacc' 5' to the gene start site (following the EcoRI 
            restriction site to have a good 5' Kozak sequence). Insert confirmed
            via Sanger Sequencing in April 2020 by Rachel Eguia. This resulted 
            in plasmid 2736. Additional cloning was conducted to delete a 21 
            amino acid region from the C-terminal end of the Spike protein. 
            Spike deletion confirmed by Sanger Sequencing in May 2020 by Rachel.
            D614 G mutation added in June 2020 by Keara Malone. Sequence 
            confirmed by Rachel Eguia and Kate Crawford.
